Act/Order.text: Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1951[7]

Explanation.text: The Indian Constitution came into effect and new constituencies were created.
Patiala and East Punjab States Union (PEPSU) was merged with Punjab and the number of constituencies of the enlarged state was increased.

Act/Order.text: Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1961[10]

Explanation.text: There were changes in the number and reservation status of constituencies. Two-member constituencies were abolished.
The new state of Haryana was created from the south-east parts of Punjab. Some districts of Punjab were also merged with Himachal Pradesh.

Act/Order.text: Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1976[14]

Explanation.text: There were changes in the number and reservation status of constituencies.
There were changes in the reservation status and area covered by constituencies.
